Paper 2026: Common run configuration

Each storm folder (ordinary/ and supercell/) contains the two runtime inputs needed to run:
  - namelist.input
  - carp_force

All runs use the paper versions of these CM1 source files:
  - base.F   (sounding + wind options, including the ordinary-storm wind modifications)
  - init3d.F (Carpenter forcing implementation; reads carp_force)

To apply this setup to a separate CM1 tree: copy base.F and init3d.F from this repo into your
CM1 source directory (overwriting), rebuild, then run using the storm-specific namelist.input
and carp_force.

Base-state choices used in this paper:
  - isnd = 5 for all runs (Weisman–Klemp sounding)
  - supercell: iwnd = 2 (WK quarter-circle)
  - ordinary:  iwnd = 1 (RKW-type; only udep2 and uconst2 modified)
